{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d62aec4d-d8ac-422f-b833-d26ac6f30e4f","content":"The issue is the F# file compilation order. In F#, files can only reference types/modules from files listed *above* them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but is listed first.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_ZFfUrBXBLwCH2MNQObLJQW","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-4ae972ae89e74c81bd2fb721b846894f/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-4ae972ae89e74c81bd2fb721b846894f/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"892d9e9a-f78d-48cd-8fc7-c749c23d6297","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference types/modules defined in files that appear *before* them in the compilation order. \n\nLooking at the .fsproj file:\n1. `Services.fs` is listed first\n2. `Domain.fs` is listed second\n3. `Program.fs` is listed third\n\nBut `Services.fs` depends on `BrokenOrder.Domain` (it opens it), so `Domain.fs` must come before `Services.fs`. Similarly, `Program.fs` depends on both `Domain` and `Services`, so it should come last.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n\n\n1. `Domain.fs`\n2. `Services.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`","outputTokens":448,"requestId":"1C3B:BD1D2:B80310:D5060E:69F3FA84"},"id":"3590b6d1-4917-4ba9-b1a9-17256203c1c4","timestamp":"2026-05-01T00:57:48.197Z","parentId":"c6fa3224-6f72-4a90-9224-8ca949ba338e"}
